Subject: Support GlobalProtect CAS callback in gp-saml-gui

GlobalProtect CAS/default-browser auth may return either a base64 encoded
HTML comment with prelogin-cookie or a query string callback with
cas-as=1&un=<user>&token=<token>. WebKit may fail to navigate the custom URI
or leave it as a page link, so intercept navigation failures and scan loaded
page bodies. For CAS token callbacks, emit gateway:token so patched
OpenConnect can submit token during GP login. Also advertise CAS support and a
modern app-version during prelogin.

